emuInput.TitMainTitle: Men and women seated at three banquet tables in the Greene Hearth for John Wood retirement party
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 24, 1959, pg. 8 reads: "Rteires [sic] After 39 Years - School officials, co-workers and friends gathered around the banquet table at Greene Hearthe last Saturday to honor John Wood, custodian at Leo Weil School for 39 years, and who is retiring on Jan. 31.  Shown in above picture, from left to right, are Charles R. Freeble, principal of A. Leo Weil School; Mrs. John Wood, John Wood, honored guest; Dr. Leslie Watters, the Rev. Ramsey Bridges, William Roman, David B. Roberts, Russell Robinson, Mrs. Helen Robinson, MRs. Marian Harris, and chairman, Mrs. Katherine Williams. - Harris Photo."
